  "material_finding": "The per-block df_g fitted leakage-free to the realised WITHIN-block upper co-exceedances of the standalone loss vectors are df_NONFIN=37.866, df_FIN=8.506 (FIN/carve-out = credit, FX, liquidity). The realised within-block upper co-exceedances (p=0.90) are NON-FIN 0.1250, FIN 0.1250, cross-block 0.1719: the standalone loss vectors do NOT exhibit strong within-FIN >> cross-block tail concentration (boundary-pinned df flags [False, False]). The grouped-t at df_hat moves the component SCR to 35604.4 vs the frozen-t 39975.7 (-10.93%, down) - the DISCLOSED two-sided direction is down. The disclosed df grid confirms the lever produces within-FIN >> cross-block heterogeneity (up to +0.0561 at df_FIN=2.1) that a single pooled df cannot. Whether the grouped-t CLOSES the upward nested residual 46,638.9 is resolved by the Task 3 bootstrap; given the standalone margins show modest within-block concentration, the expectation is the copula-form residual (skew-t-reconfirmed 6,114.9) is only partially moved and the vine (Aas et al. 2009) remains the general fallback (Phase 29)."
 },
